1
00:01:23,316 --> 00:01:24,715
Hello? Who!?

2
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:26,848
No. I'm sorry,
I don't know anyone by that name

3
00:01:27,053 --> 00:01:29,112
No, listen,
I get about a hundred customers a night.

4
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:30,684
I can't keep track of them all.

5
00:01:30,890 --> 00:01:32,653
Do you know...
well tell me what he likes to eat

6
00:01:32,992 --> 00:01:33,981
Cause I remember people
by what they order.

7
00:01:34,327 --> 00:01:36,124
Not by their names.

8
00:01:36,830 --> 00:01:38,024
"Meat Loaf? "

9
00:01:38,231 --> 00:01:40,962
Well, I know a Meat Loaf
with Mashed Potatoes.

10
00:01:40,963 --> 00:01:42,531
I know Meat Loaf who likes

11
00:01:42,735 --> 00:01:46,398
Well, with Cheese Fries,
Pouched Egg, Onion Rings.

12
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,865
What? He doesn't like potatoes?

13
00:01:49,075 --> 00:01:52,442
Why don't you, well,
yeah give me your number

14
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:54,306
And if I see him, I'll
tell him to call you

15
00:01:54,814 --> 00:01:57,146
Yeah, I promise. I will. Ok bye.

16
00:02:00,687 --> 00:02:02,552
He's 5'11 with dark brown hair.

17
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:05,349
Sorry, I can't think of any Meat Loafs
with Cheese Fries

18
00:02:05,558 --> 00:02:07,253
or Onion Rings or Pouched Eggs.

19
00:02:07,527 --> 00:02:09,757
Or Fried Fillet of Fish
that match that description.

20
00:02:10,196 --> 00:02:12,221
Last time we were here,
I think he had the pork chops.

21
00:02:12,632 --> 00:02:13,621
Oh why didn't you say so?

22
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,435
That's because we supposedly
have the best pork chops in the city.

23
00:02:16,669 --> 00:02:17,226
You ever tried them?

24
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:18,232
No, I haven't.

25
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:20,269
Why not?
What, are you religious or something?

26
00:02:21,274 --> 00:02:23,139
Listen, have you seen him or not?

27
00:02:24,544 --> 00:02:28,207
5'11 ". Dark brown hair. Pork chops

28
00:02:28,948 --> 00:02:31,348
I have actually.
He came in here for dinner last night.

29
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:32,514
He ordered two pork chops.

30
00:02:32,785 --> 00:02:35,276
One with mashed potatoes and
one with string beans.

31
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:37,482
I guess he was hungry.

32
00:02:37,757 --> 00:02:39,122
No, he didn't eat both of them.

33
00:02:39,359 --> 00:02:41,293
Our portions are too big
for a person to eat two

34
00:02:41,594 --> 00:02:43,687
No, one was for him and one was
for his girlfriend

35
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,325
Look! Just get to the point...

36
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:48,327
Don't... Don't change the subject!

37
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,868
Are you seeing someone else?

38
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:54,162
Who is she?

39
00:02:57,377 --> 00:02:58,844
I hope you both drop dead!

40
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:21,162
If someone comes in here looking for me

41
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:22,527
give him these keys.

42
00:03:23,236 --> 00:03:23,998
What do I tell him?

43
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:25,499
Tell him he's an asshole!

44
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:31,869
Taxi!

45
00:03:55,635 --> 00:03:57,193
Hey, did he pick up the keys?

46
00:03:57,937 --> 00:03:59,199
No, not yet

47
00:04:10,316 --> 00:04:11,715
Do you have an extra cigarette?

48
00:04:11,884 --> 00:04:12,851
Sure.

49
00:04:15,121 --> 00:04:16,315
Rolled it myself.

50
00:04:16,556 --> 00:04:17,420
Thanks.

51
00:04:27,533 --> 00:04:28,557
You okay?

52
00:04:29,235 --> 00:04:30,099
Yeah.

53
00:04:31,704 --> 00:04:33,467
I haven't had one in a while

54
00:04:33,706 --> 00:04:35,367
I only smoke when I get stressed out.

55
00:04:35,575 --> 00:04:36,439
Well, you shouldn't worry so much.

56
00:04:36,843 --> 00:04:38,276
That way you'll avoid lung cancer.

57
00:04:41,848 --> 00:04:43,110
Do you think she's pretty?

58
00:04:44,217 --> 00:04:44,876
Who?

59
00:04:45,084 --> 00:04:46,346
The girl he was in here with.

60
00:04:47,854 --> 00:04:50,618
Oh, she was okay I guess... I mean.

61
00:04:50,857 --> 00:04:53,189
Not the type I would prefer
to have my pork chops with

62
00:04:53,493 --> 00:04:56,360
but "each man to his own", right?

63
00:04:57,263 --> 00:04:58,628
Yeah right.

64
00:05:36,369 --> 00:05:37,233
Hello.

65
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:38,494
Hey.

66
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:47,671
I need someone to talk to.

67
00:05:52,585 --> 00:05:54,177
Do you think he'll pick up the keys?

68
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:55,780
I don't know

69
00:05:56,122 --> 00:05:58,420
I've had customers
leaving keys here for years.

70
00:05:58,658 --> 00:06:00,182
Sometimes they pick
them up in a few days.

71
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:02,553
Sometimes it takes a few weeks.

72
00:06:03,096 --> 00:06:04,529
Well, what about most of the time?

73
00:06:04,764 --> 00:06:07,392
Most of the time, the
keys stay in the jar.

74
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:15,306
Well why do you keep them?

75
00:06:15,775 --> 00:06:16,799
You should just throw them out.

76
00:06:17,009 --> 00:06:17,998
No.

77
00:06:19,312 --> 00:06:20,836
No I couldn't do that.

78
00:06:22,448 --> 00:06:23,506
Why not?

79
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:26,079
If I threw these keys away

80
00:06:26,319 --> 00:06:29,083
then those doors will be closed forever.

81
00:06:29,355 --> 00:06:30,879
And that shouldn't be up to me to decide.

82
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:33,383
Should it?

83
00:06:39,031 --> 00:06:40,931
Guess I'm just looking for a reason.

84
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:45,636
Well, from my observations

85
00:06:46,973 --> 00:06:49,703
sometimes it's better off not knowing

86
00:06:50,042 --> 00:06:54,172
and other times there's
no reason to be found.

87
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:56,075
Everything has a reason.

88
00:06:59,952 --> 00:07:01,510
It's like these pies and cakes.

89
00:07:02,288 --> 00:07:03,755
At the end of every night

90
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:07,817
the cheesecake and the apple pie
are always completely gone.

91
00:07:08,027 --> 00:07:09,358
The peach cobbler

92
00:07:09,662 --> 00:07:12,460
and the chocolate mousse cake
are nearly finished.

93
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:17,501
But there's always a whole
blueberry pie left untouched.

94
00:07:19,405 --> 00:07:21,236
So what's wrong with the blueberry pie?

95
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,136
There's nothing's wrong
with the blueberry pie.

96
00:07:23,409 --> 00:07:24,433
It's just people make other choices.

97
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:26,075
You can't blame the blueberry pie.

98
00:07:26,345 --> 00:07:28,074
It's just no one wants it.

99
00:07:30,216 --> 00:07:31,205
Wait!

100
00:07:33,085 --> 00:07:34,382
I want a piece.

101
00:07:34,654 --> 00:07:35,678
With ice cream?

102
00:07:38,925 --> 00:07:39,892
Leave it to me.

103
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:48,155
Here we go.

104
00:07:49,035 --> 00:07:50,229
I hope you enjoy it.

105
00:07:50,436 --> 00:07:51,300
Thanks.

106
00:08:09,188 --> 00:08:10,177
It's not bad.

107
00:08:10,389 --> 00:08:11,321
Really?

108
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,218
You should try some.

109
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:18,056
No, I'm alright. I have my own.

110
00:09:12,985 --> 00:09:15,613
Will you tell me the stories
behind those other keys?

111
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:18,857
What for?

112
00:09:21,027 --> 00:09:23,689
I just wondered how
they all ended up here.

113
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:28,667
Pick one.

114
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:37,804
Those belonged to a young
couple a few years ago.

115
00:09:38,044 --> 00:09:39,170
They were naive enough to believe

116
00:09:39,445 --> 00:09:41,310
that they were gonna spend the
rest of their lives together.

117
00:09:42,782 --> 00:09:43,908
Well, what happened?

118
00:09:44,684 --> 00:09:45,981
Life happened.

119
00:09:46,886 --> 00:09:48,649
Things happened. Yeah, time happened.

120
00:09:50,289 --> 00:09:52,655
It's pretty much always
the case more or less.

121
00:09:54,994 --> 00:09:57,189
Or maybe one of them ran off
with someone else.

122
00:09:57,396 --> 00:09:59,261
Maybe the feelings just went away.

123
00:10:05,871 --> 00:10:07,099
What about these?

124
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:10,008
Those belonged to a little old lady

125
00:10:10,242 --> 00:10:12,369
Her best friend would pick them up
and come to visit her.

126
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:14,239
She dropped them off
and I never saw her again.

127
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,674
I presumed, I mean, she was pretty old.

128
00:10:15,881 --> 00:10:18,406
I presumed she passed away or something.

129
00:10:21,654 --> 00:10:23,053
What about these?

130
00:10:25,691 --> 00:10:28,319
These keys used to
belong to a young lad

131
00:10:28,995 --> 00:10:30,485
from Manchester England

132
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:33,765
who made plans and had dreams

133
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:35,729
of running every
marathon in this country

134
00:10:36,068 --> 00:10:37,296
starting in New York.

135
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:41,406
He was going to write a journal
about his experiences

136
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:44,607
and ended up running a cafe.

137
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:48,146
Later they were given to a Russian girl

138
00:10:49,782 --> 00:10:51,613
who loved collecting keys

139
00:10:52,618 --> 00:10:54,017
and watching sunsets.

140
00:10:55,121 --> 00:10:58,557
Unfortunately,
she loved sunsets more than the keys

141
00:10:58,858 --> 00:11:00,416
and ended up disappearing into one.

142
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:04,921
Why didn't you go looking for her?

143
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:12,594
When I was little

144
00:11:12,872 --> 00:11:15,102
me mum used to take me to the park
on weekends

145
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:17,305
She said if I ever got lost.

146
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:21,209
I had to stay in one place
so that she'd find me.

147
00:11:21,547 --> 00:11:22,445
Does that work?

148
00:11:23,149 --> 00:11:24,343
Not really.

149
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:27,276
She got lost once looking for me.

150
00:11:27,987 --> 00:11:29,477
Eh, you want some more ice cream?

151
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:30,750
No thanks.

152
00:11:30,956 --> 00:11:31,752
You sure?

153
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:33,185
Yeah I'm fine. Thanks.

154
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:15,534
You're late.

155
00:12:18,137 --> 00:12:19,365
Same as usual?

156
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:32,676
No thanks.

157
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:40,724
Can I have my keys back?

158
00:12:41,794 --> 00:12:43,227
Yeah, sure.

159
00:12:47,533 --> 00:12:48,522
So...

160
00:12:49,802 --> 00:12:52,134
You two have patched things up then?

161
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:55,539
Thanks.

162
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,405
Lousy bloody camera.

163
00:13:34,213 --> 00:13:35,145
Hey!

164
00:13:35,381 --> 00:13:37,941
Alright. Come on. Break it... Alright!

165
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,981
Take it outside. Take it out...

166
00:13:40,252 --> 00:13:40,775
None of your business cupcake!

167
00:13:41,086 --> 00:13:41,848
Don't start with me mate!

168
00:13:42,121 --> 00:13:43,452
Don't you start... Come here!

169
00:13:43,722 --> 00:13:44,620
Right you come here

170
00:13:45,024 --> 00:13:46,184
Get out of my place!

171
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:49,921
Don't start with me!

172
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:51,026
Get out!

173
00:13:51,764 --> 00:13:53,857
Hey you haven't paid yet!

174
00:14:16,088 --> 00:14:17,248
Can I have a tissue?

175
00:14:17,456 --> 00:14:18,320
What happened?

176
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:19,655
Did he hit you?

177
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:20,826
No!

178
00:14:21,126 --> 00:14:22,218
Well what?

179
00:14:23,562 --> 00:14:25,462
I got mugged on the subway.

180
00:14:25,998 --> 00:14:27,966
I thought Pork Chop lived around here?

181
00:14:29,468 --> 00:14:30,628
He does.

182
00:14:31,003 --> 00:14:32,834
What were you doing on the subway?

183
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:35,031
Well...

184
00:14:35,941 --> 00:14:38,205
I just needed some
time to prepare myself.

185
00:14:40,312 --> 00:14:42,439
I was gonna get off in a few stops.

186
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:45,076
I don't know, I just.

187
00:14:45,284 --> 00:14:47,115
The next thing I knew,
I ended up in the Bronx.

188
00:14:48,087 --> 00:14:50,419
That's a very interesting
way to prepare yourself

189
00:14:56,662 --> 00:14:58,721
I've never been very
good at confrontation

190
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:03,162
Some people enjoy it.

191
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:05,161
Not me.

192
00:15:09,808 --> 00:15:11,400
Hey, are you alright?

193
00:15:11,677 --> 00:15:12,974
Should we call the police or something?

194
00:15:16,348 --> 00:15:17,280
No.

195
00:15:19,785 --> 00:15:21,946
No, he didn't get away with very much.

196
00:15:23,289 --> 00:15:25,689
Especially after I
kicked him in the balls.

197
00:15:26,692 --> 00:15:27,681
You didn't.

198
00:15:36,335 --> 00:15:38,064
Wait, what happened to you?

199
00:15:41,874 --> 00:15:44,001
I ate too much chocolate .

200
00:15:52,484 --> 00:15:53,849
What's wrong with your camera?

201
00:15:54,053 --> 00:15:55,145
Oh, I don't know.

202
00:15:55,387 --> 00:15:58,447
It's been in a lousy
mood these past few days.

203
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:02,860
It doesn't really keep
people from stealing, does it?

204
00:16:03,162 --> 00:16:04,094
No.

205
00:16:06,732 --> 00:16:07,858
Not really.

206
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:11,194
But I like having it around, 'cause

207
00:16:13,539 --> 00:16:15,200
for me it's like my diary.

208
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:16,638
You know?

209
00:16:23,716 --> 00:16:25,911
Some nights, I watch the tapes back and

210
00:16:27,386 --> 00:16:29,877
I'm amazed at how much I've missed.

211
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:33,883
That's going on right in front of me.

212
00:16:36,061 --> 00:16:37,790
You must have a lot of tapes.

213
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:41,591
I don't keep them all.

214
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,097
I'm not that weird.

215
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:46,404
Only the highlights

216
00:16:58,550 --> 00:16:59,676
Can I take a look?

217
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:01,851
Sure.

218
00:17:03,188 --> 00:17:04,177
Come around.

219
00:21:17,242 --> 00:21:20,370
She left behind her set of keys
and disappeared that night.

220
00:21:58,216 --> 00:22:01,583
How do you say goodbye to someone
you can't imagine living without?

221
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:04,678
I didn't say goodbye.

222
00:22:08,860 --> 00:22:10,350
I didn't say anything.

223
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:16,331
I just walked away.

224
00:22:18,970 --> 00:22:20,403
At the end of that night.

225
00:22:20,639 --> 00:22:23,437
I decided to take the longest way
to cross the street.

226
00:22:32,684 --> 00:22:33,981
Dear Jeremy.

227
00:22:34,953 --> 00:22:36,818
As you can see by this postcard

228
00:22:37,055 --> 00:22:38,545
I'm now in Memphis, Tennessee.

229
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:41,190
Hey Lizzy, hurry up with
those damn pick-ups will ya!

230
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:41,849
Coming!

231
00:22:42,094 --> 00:22:42,617
Come on hustle it!

232
00:22:42,928 --> 00:22:44,953
It took me a long time to get here

233
00:22:45,297 --> 00:22:47,356
And I'm not sure how
long I'll be staying

234
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:51,061
During the day, I work
at a diner downtown

235
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:53,965
I haven't been able to sleep at night

236
00:22:54,206 --> 00:22:57,175
so I've also taken a
waitressing job at a bar

237
00:22:58,510 --> 00:23:02,503
It's kind of a dive,
but the tips are pretty good

238
00:23:03,014 --> 00:23:05,141
Working two jobs is exhausting

239
00:23:05,584 --> 00:23:07,313
But at least it keeps me busy

240
00:23:07,819 --> 00:23:11,448
and most importantly,
it keeps my mind away from him

241
00:23:43,321 --> 00:23:43,844
Hi girl

242
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:44,987
Hey Sandy

243
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:46,655
You going home?

244
00:23:47,492 --> 00:23:48,652
Let me put it this way

245
00:23:49,394 --> 00:23:50,793
I'm getting up out of here

246
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:54,364
I wish I could go

247
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,893
What's wrong?

248
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:57,295
That guy at the bar

249
00:23:57,836 --> 00:23:59,463
I don't think he's ever gonna leave

250
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:02,830
Oh you're talking about Arnie?

251
00:24:03,108 --> 00:24:04,006
Child, don't worry about him.

252
00:24:04,443 --> 00:24:06,070
He probably just lost track of time

253
00:24:06,311 --> 00:24:07,403
But now if you need to get going

254
00:24:07,679 --> 00:24:09,510
You just bring his check to him,
have him sign it

255
00:24:09,881 --> 00:24:11,041
Travis runs a tab for him

256
00:24:11,516 --> 00:24:12,847
Well, does he always stay this late?

257
00:24:13,452 --> 00:24:14,749
Always

258
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:16,949
You stick around here
you see for yourself

259
00:24:17,689 --> 00:24:18,519
Have a good night darlin'

260
00:24:18,757 --> 00:24:20,281
You too. Good night

261
00:24:31,203 --> 00:24:32,500
Here's your check

262
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:51,520
Just eight?

263
00:24:53,158 --> 00:24:55,991
I coulda sworn I had at least nine

264
00:24:56,962 --> 00:24:58,429
No, just eight

265
00:25:00,632 --> 00:25:01,997
Do you have a pen?

266
00:25:02,801 --> 00:25:03,825
Yeah

267
00:25:07,873 --> 00:25:09,500
I don't recognize you

268
00:25:10,141 --> 00:25:12,200
You new around here or something?

269
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:13,809
I just started a few nights ago

270
00:25:14,145 --> 00:25:15,271
Oh

271
00:25:21,987 --> 00:25:23,454
Have you got a name?

272
00:25:24,789 --> 00:25:25,778
Lizzie

273
00:25:26,091 --> 00:25:27,285
Lizzie

274
