00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:46,128
I guess you can give it to Travis and

551
00:52:46,363 --> 00:52:47,762
he can mark the debt paid

552
00:52:49,332 --> 00:52:51,197
I'll give it to Travis tonight

553
00:52:52,369 --> 00:52:54,462
Shock might give him a heart attack

554
00:53:10,253 --> 00:53:12,312
I have a favor to ask you

555
00:53:15,892 --> 00:53:17,757
Could you keep his bill hanging?

556
00:53:21,164 --> 00:53:23,098
So they don't forget him too soon?

557
00:53:27,737 --> 00:53:28,601
OK

558
00:53:59,169 --> 00:54:02,764
I guess for Sue Lynne,
leaving this town was like dying

559
00:54:06,643 --> 00:54:09,203
I wonder how people
would remember Arnie

560
00:54:11,781 --> 00:54:14,477
When you're gone,
all that's left behind are the memories

561
00:54:14,784 --> 00:54:16,581
you created in other people's lives

562
00:54:19,322 --> 00:54:21,620
or just a couple of items on a bill

563
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:32,933
I began receiving postcards
from her regularly

564
00:54:33,903 --> 00:54:38,135
Instead of calling strangers,
I decided to change my strategy

565
00:54:39,409 --> 00:54:42,310
It was tiring writing the
same words over and over again

566
00:54:43,046 --> 00:54:45,708
but all worth it
if only one of them reached her

567
00:55:04,367 --> 00:55:07,393
I always had the feeling
I could say anything to you.

568
00:55:09,172 --> 00:55:11,663
Enclosed is a bill I've created for you

569
00:55:11,875 --> 00:55:13,706
in memory of our time together

570
00:55:16,246 --> 00:55:18,476
I wonder how you remember me

571
00:55:21,384 --> 00:55:23,909
As the girl who liked blueberry pies

572
00:55:27,590 --> 00:55:29,524
or the girl with the broken heart?

573
00:56:53,877 --> 00:56:55,742
Still rolling your own cigarettes?

574
00:57:01,684 --> 00:57:02,651
You want one?

575
00:57:03,586 --> 00:57:04,553
Yeah

576
00:57:19,836 --> 00:57:21,235
Tastes different

577
00:57:22,439 --> 00:57:24,600
It's probably just been
in my pocket too long

578
00:57:29,712 --> 00:57:32,510
It's a shame you can't
smoke in cafes anymore

579
00:57:32,816 --> 00:57:34,511
You can't smoke anywhere anymore

580
00:57:36,352 --> 00:57:38,320
You should've changed the place

581
00:57:39,088 --> 00:57:40,988
It's not that much different

582
00:57:41,791 --> 00:57:43,258
I've been meaning to buy new chairs

583
00:57:43,493 --> 00:57:44,983
but I couldn't never
find any that match

584
00:57:45,829 --> 00:57:47,456
the tables and the tiles

585
00:57:48,331 --> 00:57:49,559
Shouldn't be hard

586
00:57:50,300 --> 00:57:53,064
Maybe you're just looking
in the wrong places or

587
00:57:53,369 --> 00:57:55,599
maybe you're just sentimental

588
00:58:00,176 --> 00:58:01,575
You look lovely

589
00:58:01,878 --> 00:58:03,812
I'm starting to look like my mom

590
00:58:04,013 --> 00:58:05,571
It's better than looking like your dad

591
00:58:05,815 --> 00:58:07,043
I've seen photos of him

592
00:58:16,926 --> 00:58:18,689
You still have the keys?

593
00:58:20,964 --> 00:58:23,797
Yeah... I always remember what you said

594
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:26,093
about never throwing
them away, about never

595
00:58:26,402 --> 00:58:29,303
closing those doors forever. I remember

596
00:58:30,640 --> 00:58:34,132
Sometimes, even if you have the keys

597
00:58:34,911 --> 00:58:36,708
those doors still

598
00:58:37,247 --> 00:58:39,408
can't be opened, can they?

599
00:58:42,619 --> 00:58:44,382
Even if the door is open

600
00:58:44,621 --> 00:58:47,112
the person you're looking
for may not be there, Katya

601
00:58:54,664 --> 00:58:56,894
A few years ago, I had a dream

602
00:58:58,701 --> 00:59:00,328
It began in the summer

603
00:59:00,670 --> 00:59:02,934
and was over by the following spring

604
00:59:05,275 --> 00:59:07,835
In between, there was
as many unhappy nights

605
00:59:08,144 --> 00:59:09,577
as there were happy days

606
00:59:10,713 --> 00:59:13,443
Most of them took place in this cafe

607
00:59:16,519 --> 00:59:17,884
And then one night

608
00:59:18,087 --> 00:59:20,214
a door slammed and the dream was over

609
00:59:37,807 --> 00:59:39,468
I should be going

610
00:59:40,310 --> 00:59:42,574
I have to catch a flight in the morning

611
00:59:43,580 --> 00:59:45,480
Thanks for the smoke.

612
00:59:53,856 --> 00:59:56,154
You know,
I didn't even think you'd still be here

613
00:59:57,193 --> 00:59:58,285
Why'd you come?

614
01:00:02,932 --> 01:00:06,891
I guess I just wanted to see
if I could remember

615
01:00:07,503 --> 01:00:09,061
what it felt like

616
01:00:21,217 --> 01:00:22,809
Goodbye, Jeremy

617
01:00:31,527 --> 01:00:32,687
Bye, Katya

618
01:00:49,212 --> 01:00:50,144
Cocktails?

619
01:00:50,513 --> 01:00:51,537
A screwdriver, please

620
01:00:51,781 --> 01:00:52,475
Here you go

621
01:00:52,682 --> 01:00:53,910
Dear Jeremy

622
01:00:55,118 --> 01:00:57,814
I've always been
fascinated by card players

623
01:00:59,122 --> 01:01:02,057
They risk everything on
their instincts and their luck

624
01:01:03,893 --> 01:01:05,918
I wonder if I would be
able to make the same moves

625
01:01:06,229 --> 01:01:07,560
in their position

626
01:01:08,865 --> 01:01:10,628
Or would I just fold?

627
01:01:12,702 --> 01:01:14,670
Sweetheart, do you mind?

628
01:01:18,041 --> 01:01:20,566
Uh-oh look at that

629
01:01:21,010 --> 01:01:22,602
She gets another one this kid

630
01:01:22,879 --> 01:01:23,903
You know Leslie you got that fancy Jag

631
01:01:24,280 --> 01:01:25,645
you working on a Rolls Royce now?

632
01:01:27,183 --> 01:01:30,448
Aloha, you forgot to tip the waitress

633
01:01:30,820 --> 01:01:32,447
Actually I didn't forget dick

634
01:01:32,789 --> 01:01:33,687
Because I never tip

635
01:01:33,923 --> 01:01:35,447
What do you mean you never tip?

636
01:01:35,725 --> 01:01:37,090
I mean Harlan can afford
to pay his own people

637
01:01:37,393 --> 01:01:38,155
I don't know why I have to

638
01:01:38,361 --> 01:01:39,828
You can be cheap or you can be lucky

639
01:01:40,063 --> 01:01:42,623
but you can't be both.
Not in the long run

640
01:01:42,899 --> 01:01:44,389
Here ya go, toots

641
01:01:44,701 --> 01:01:47,192
That is from Mr. Aloha over there

642
01:01:47,670 --> 01:01:49,900
He's gonna pay me back,
he doesn't know it yet

643
01:01:50,940 --> 01:01:51,770
Thanks

644
01:01:52,008 --> 01:01:53,532
Your luck just went south

645
01:01:54,844 --> 01:01:56,038
Who's blinds?

646
01:01:57,447 --> 01:02:01,042
Working long hours in the casino
makes you lose track of the time

647
01:02:02,852 --> 01:02:05,412
And I'm never sure
whether it's day or night

648
01:02:06,789 --> 01:02:10,555
But at least I don't have to worry
about my sleeping problem anymore

649
01:02:11,928 --> 01:02:14,260
Somehow it's gone away

650
01:02:23,973 --> 01:02:25,634
How much you got left, sweet cheeks?

651
01:02:25,842 --> 01:02:26,900
Because that's what I bet

652
01:02:31,247 --> 01:02:32,441
Eighteen-twenty

653
01:02:35,218 --> 01:02:37,083
You on a big draw, Aloha?

654
01:02:37,587 --> 01:02:39,885
Because otherwise
you're just about dead

655
01:02:51,367 --> 01:02:53,062
You are on a big draw

656
01:02:53,536 --> 01:02:55,026
Twelve outs twice

657
01:02:55,505 --> 01:02:56,665
You wanna do business?

658
01:02:56,973 --> 01:02:57,997
Make me an offer

659
01:02:58,241 --> 01:03:00,300
How about you take six
hundred and I take a thousand

660
01:03:00,676 --> 01:03:01,870
and we gamble for the rest?

661
01:03:02,945 --> 01:03:04,207
I say I need more than that

662
01:03:04,413 --> 01:03:05,573
Doesn't seem fair to you?

663
01:03:05,815 --> 01:03:06,782
I feel like gambling

664
01:03:07,016 --> 01:03:08,176
So what do you want me to do?

665
01:03:08,618 --> 01:03:09,846
You heard the man.

666
01:03:10,453 --> 01:03:12,921
He wants to gamble. Deal

667
01:03:16,492 --> 01:03:19,950
Bet you wish you took that
six hundred now,huh Aloha?

668
01:03:20,797 --> 01:03:22,697
Don't get too cocky little girl

669
01:03:22,899 --> 01:03:24,389
Five of hearts still in that deck

670
01:03:24,700 --> 01:03:25,826
Oh come on

671
01:03:26,969 --> 01:03:29,733
We can all dream, Aloha

672
01:03:30,206 --> 01:03:31,400
I wish you luck

673
01:03:32,708 --> 01:03:33,504
Why don't you deal the card?

674
01:03:33,676 --> 01:03:34,472
Fine

675
01:03:38,681 --> 01:03:40,945
Wait, wait, how did you do that?

676
01:03:41,617 --> 01:03:43,016
Ok I swear I wasn't cheating

677
01:03:43,386 --> 01:03:44,512
I had the deck in my hand

678
01:03:46,122 --> 01:03:47,783
Pass it to the sugardaddy here

679
01:03:48,357 --> 01:03:49,984
I'm telling my grandkids about that one

680
01:03:55,665 --> 01:03:56,996
Maybe

681
01:03:58,568 --> 01:04:01,366
A salad. That'd be healthy, right?

682
01:04:01,704 --> 01:04:03,695
I don't think I could get it down though

683
01:04:03,906 --> 01:04:05,498
All that chewing and swallowing

684
01:04:07,443 --> 01:04:09,604
Maybe I'll get some eggs

685
01:04:10,479 --> 01:04:11,673
Protein, right?

686
01:04:11,948 --> 01:04:12,972
How would you like them?

687
01:04:13,182 --> 01:04:15,412
Tied in a knot and nailed to the floor

688
01:04:15,785 --> 01:04:18,015
Or maybe you can just
crack 'em over my head

689
01:04:18,387 --> 01:04:20,014
and let 'em trickle down my cheeks

690
01:04:23,593 --> 01:04:24,753
Beth

691
01:04:26,262 --> 01:04:28,526
Why don't I just go ask them right now?

692
01:04:32,201 --> 01:04:35,637
So who is gonna lend me a grand
so I can get back in?

693
01:04:36,706 --> 01:04:40,005
Sam, come on, this is
me we're talking about

694
01:04:40,743 --> 01:04:44,179
Why can't you just advance me the cash

695
01:04:44,413 --> 01:04:47,211
and I will wire you back the money
within 24 hours

696
01:04:47,450 --> 01:04:49,611
You won't even have a chance to miss it

697
01:04:51,020 --> 01:04:52,146
Yeah?

698
01:04:52,521 --> 01:04:54,284
Well fuck you very much!

699
01:04:58,761 --> 01:04:59,989
Rough night, huh?

700
01:05:00,196 --> 01:05:01,493
You could say that

701
01:05:05,167 --> 01:05:06,896
How did you wind up in this hellhole?

702
01:05:07,136 --> 01:05:08,797
The bus just dropped me off here

703
01:05:09,038 --> 01:05:09,868
Where'd you come from?

704
01:05:10,072 --> 01:05:10,970
New York

705
01:05:11,207 --> 01:05:13,869
You came all the way here
from New York on a bus?

706
01:05:14,477 --> 01:05:15,671
Sounds awful

707
01:05:16,979 --> 01:05:19,243
Actually, I was on quite a few of them

708
01:05:20,449 --> 01:05:22,144
You must love buses

709
01:05:22,652 --> 01:05:24,586
I wanna get a car but

710
01:05:25,154 --> 01:05:26,917
it's not easy saving money

711
01:05:27,623 --> 01:05:28,988
How much you got?

712
01:05:29,258 --> 01:05:31,920
About twenty-one, twenty-two hundred

713
01:05:37,099 --> 01:05:38,259
Hey Beth

714
01:05:41,304 --> 01:05:43,238
I've got a proposition for you

715
01:05:43,472 --> 01:05:44,996
What kind of proposition?

716
01:05:45,374 --> 01:05:46,966
See, I need a stake

717
01:05:48,344 --> 01:05:49,971
There's a man I could call in Vegas

718
01:05:50,279 --> 01:05:52,179
but I don't want to do that

719
01:05:52,615 --> 01:05:54,378
I'm gonna win that game

720
01:05:54,617 --> 01:05:56,710
I'm a stronger player than any of them

721
01:05:57,987 --> 01:06:00,683
If you give me a chance
I'm gonna clean their clocks.

722
01:06:03,893 --> 01:06:05,360
How much do you need?

723
01:06:05,995 --> 01:06:08,486
Well your twenty two hundred
would get me back in

724
01:06:09,098 --> 01:06:11,692
And then, once I cash out

725
01:06:12,868 --> 01:06:15,769
you'll get your money back plus a third
of my winnings

726
01:06:16,372 --> 01:06:17,771
But what if you lose?

727
01:06:19,842 --> 01:06:23,778
If I lose, you get my car

728
01:06:24,613 --> 01:06:26,274
It's a brand new Jag

729
01:06:26,515 --> 01:06:27,812
This way

730
01:06:28,184 --> 01:06:29,276
whatever happens

731
01:06:29,518 --> 01:06:31,884
you've got your ass covered
from here to Houston

732
01:06:36,258 --> 01:06:38,123
You got to give me a minute here

733
01:06:38,661 --> 01:06:40,094
It's been a long night

734
01:06:45,201 --> 01:06:47,761
I got an empty stomach.
Just give me a minute

735
01:06:48,070 --> 01:06:49,332
You take your time

736
01:06:49,572 --> 01:06:52,040
I wouldn't want you
choking on your food

737
01:06:54,510 --> 01:06:55,704
Shit it's cold!

738
01:06:55,911 --> 01:06:56,935
I know

739
01:07:31,147 --> 01:07:32,273
I'll do it

740
01:07:33,816 --> 01:07:35,374
Oh my, look who's back

741
01:07:36,285 --> 01:07:39,152
I thought you'd be halfway to Vegas
in that fancy ass Jag of yours

742
01:07:39,388 --> 01:07:42,619
I figure why not let you pay for my gas

743
01:08:06,949 --> 01:08:08,382
Gotta raise again

744
01:08:09,985 --> 01:08:11,247
Five hundred

745
01:08:15,624 --> 01:08:17,319
Oh one of these days
one of us is going to have

746
01:08:17,726 --> 01:08:18,988
something when you raise!

747
01:08:19,261 --> 01:08:21,525
Listen, why don't you just wink at me
when that happens

748
01:08:21,864 --> 01:08:23,058
so I know, alright?

749
01:09:12,882 --> 01:09:13,746
Raise

750
01:09:16,852 --> 01:09:18,012
I'm all in

751
01:09:26,629 --> 01:09:27,994
You want to give me a count on that?

752
01:09:29,598 --> 01:09:32,761
Fifteen... Fifteen thirty-five

753
01:09:37,139 --> 01:09:38,299
Too rich for me

754
01:09:51,287 --> 01:09:52,447
I don't know what's worse

755
01:09:52,855 --> 01:09:54,618
That cute smile or that ugly shirt

756
01:09:58,827 --> 01:10:00,385
I'll give you some action

757
01:10:09,838 --> 01:10:10,770
Hey

758
01:10:13,175 --> 01:10:14,608
Hey, what happened?

759
01:10:15,477 --> 01:10:16,671
The car's yours

760
01:10:18,414 --> 01:10:20,075
You've got to give me a ride though

761
01:10:32,695 --> 01:10:33,719
So where we going?

762
01:10:33,929 --> 01:10:34,896
Vegas

763
01:10:41,370 --> 01:10:44,066
She said she knew some people
in Vegas who could stake her

764
01:10:44,540 --> 01:10:45,939
get her started again

765
01:10:46,775 --> 01:10:49,266
But she didn't seem
to be in a hurry to get there

766
01:10:55,818 --> 01:10:57,979
Hey Leslie, are you asleep?

767
01:10:59,588 --> 01:11:00,680
No

768
01:11:01,056 --> 01:11:04,150
I keep playing old
poker hands in my head

769
01:11:05,661 --> 01:11:06,753
You?

770
01:11:07,162 --> 01:11:08,356
Same

771
01:11:09,198 --> 01:11:10,563
Except for the poker

772
01:11:11,000 --> 01:11:12,490
What are you replaying?

773
01:11:14,003 --> 01:11:16,597
Just some stuff that happened back
in New York

774
01:11:20,843 --> 01:11:23,243
Hey, the man you told me about in Vegas

775
01:11:23,479 --> 01:11:24,673
that could give you the money

776
01:11:25,281 --> 01:11:26,270
Yeah?

777
01:11:27,583 --> 01:11:28,447
Is he a boyfriend?

778
01:11:30,019 --> 01:11:31,043
No

779
01:11:32,021 --> 01:11:34,546
I haven't had very much
luck with boyfriends

780
01:11:34,890 --> 01:11:36,084
I've had a few but

781
01:11:36,358 --> 01:11:38,849
none that I could ever ask
for anything, let alone money

782
01:11:42,798 --> 01:11:45,824
Now you want to know
who the man in Vegas is

783
01:11:46,201 --> 01:11:47,600
but you're too polite to ask

784
01:11:47,836 --> 01:11:48,825
No

785
01:11:50,205 --> 01:11:51,638
It's not important

786
01:11:53,542 --> 01:11:54,770
He's my father

787
01:11:55,644 --> 01:11:57,578
Taught me how to play poker

788
01:12:00,149 --> 01:12:02,174
He had me figuring odds
around the same time

789
01:12:02,418 --> 01:12:04,386
other kids were learning how to count

790
01:12:05,154 --> 01:12:06,587
He used to tell people

791
01:12:06,822 --> 01:12:09,382
that I thought the number
that came after ten

792
01:12:09,658 --> 01:12:10,818
was Jack

793
01:12:13,729 --> 01:12:18,132
So I can ask him for
money or anything, but

794
01:12:20,869 --> 01:12:21,893
I won't

795
01:12:35,217 --> 01:12:38,983
Trust everyone but always cut the cards

796
01:12:39,154 --> 01:12:41,213
Best thing my father ever taught me

797
01:12:42,024 --> 01:12:43,389
You know what that means?

798
01:12:43,592 --> 01:12:46,254
It means never trust anybody

799
01:12:47,363 --> 01:12:48,796
If you're so good at reading people

800
01:12:49,031 --> 01:12:49,861
Then why did I lose?

801
01:12:50,032 --> 01:12:50,999
Yeah

802
01:12:51,333 --> 01:12:53,198
Because you can't always win

803
01:12:53,535 --> 01:12:56,060
You can beat players
but you can't beat luck

804
01:12:57,039 --> 01:12:58,768
Sometimes your rhythm's off

805
01:12:59,208 --> 01:13:01,768
you read the person right
but still do the wrong thing

806
01:13:02,044 --> 01:13:03,011
Because you trust them?

807
01:13:03,612 --> 01:13:05,978
Because you can't even trust yourself

808
01:13:06,882 --> 01:13:07,849
Shit

809
01:13:10,586 --> 01:13:12,019
Nobody I want to hear from

810
01:13:12,254 --> 01:13:12,913
Nobody?

811
01:13:13,188 --> 01:13:14,246
Nobody!

812
01:13:29,671 --> 01:13:31,229
How did you get this number?

813
01:13:31,507 --> 01:13:34,305
You know this is the third time
this month I've have change it?

814
01:13:34,843 --> 01:13:37,277
Just leave me the hell
alone! Stop calling!

815
01:13:40,416 --> 01:13:41,474
Dammit!

816
01:13:41,950 --> 01:13:43,542
Beth, answer it for me

817
01:13:44,186 --> 01:13:45,153
What do you want me to say?

818
01:13:45,320 --> 01:13:47,447
Tell them its the wrong number
and not to call again

819
01:13:47,656 --> 01:13:48,588
Okay

820
01:13:50,025 --> 01:13:51,117
Hello?

821
01:13:52,161 --> 01:13:53,651
Sorry, you have-

822
01:13:54,763 --> 01:13:55,991
From where?

823
01:13:57,699 --> 01:13:58,825
Okay

824
01:14:00,536 --> 01:14:02,401
Okay... you sure?

825
01:14:03,739 --> 01:14:06,173
Okay, thank you... bye

826
01:14:09,144 --> 01:14:11,442
It was someone from a hospital in Vegas

827
01:14:12,815 --> 01:14:14,510
They said your dad's there

828
01:14:15,517 --> 01:14:17,109
And they said he's dying

829
01:14:20,189 --> 01:14:21,349
Son of a bitch

830
01:14:22,891 --> 01:14:25,416
That man... always dying

831
01:14:34,937 --> 01:14:36,529
It's a trick, okay?

832
01:14:37,406 --> 01:14:39,101
He's pulled this on me before

833
01:14:39,541 --> 01:14:41,475
Says he has to see me, he's dying

834
01:14:41,710 --> 01:14:42,574
And then

835
01:14:42,911 --> 01:14:44,776
you know how many times
I've fallen for that?

836
01:14:44,980 --> 01:14:47,278
But it was someone from the
hospital that called it wasn't him

837
01:14:47,583 --> 01:14:48,675
So what Beth?

838
01:14:49,318 --> 01:14:50,615
You think he couldn't pay someone

839
01:14:50,886 --> 01:14:52,444
to make the phone call for him?

840
01:14:53,689 --> 01:14:56,852
I swear, is there
anyone you don't trust?

841
01:14:58,193 --> 01:15:00,889
Well he must really want to see
you to make up a story like that

842
01:15:26,522 --> 01:15:29,355
Geez, you are just
dying to ask me something

843
01:15:29,825 --> 01:15:30,382
What?

844
01:15:30,692 --> 01:15:31,488
I didn't say anything

845
01:15:31,727 --> 01:15:33,490
You didn't have to. I can read you

846
01:15:33,729 --> 01:15:35,128
I can even guess what you wanna ask

847
01:15:36,832 --> 01:15:37,958
You wanna ask

848
01:15:39,234 --> 01:15:42,067
"What if he is dying? "
"What if the message is legit? "

849
01:15:42,404 --> 01:15:43,371
Well what if he is?

850
01:15:47,309 --> 01:15:48,970
The thing is Beth

851
01:15:49,478 --> 01:15:50,740
I don't care

852
01:15:51,213 --> 01:15:52,703
He lives, he dies

853
01:15:53,582 --> 01:15:54,879
whatever

854
01:15:55,517 --> 01:15:57,075
I don't fucking care

855
01:16:06,662 --> 01:16:07,959
You're lying

856
01:16:30,252 --> 01:16:31,184
I'm not going in there

857
01:16:31,386 --> 01:16:32,114
What?

858
01:16:32,454 --> 01:16:34,945
I can't. What- what if I go in there

859
01:16:35,223 --> 01:16:37,851
and he's just sitting up in his room

860
01:16:38,193 --> 01:16:40,388
with his dead beat
friends playing gin rummy

861
01:16:40,662 --> 01:16:44,894
or, I dunno, detoxing,
getting a mole removed

862
01:16:45,233 --> 01:16:46,257
You know it's more serious than that

863
01:16:46,501 --> 01:16:48,560
No, I don't know that and neither do you

864
01:16:52,741 --> 01:16:55,608
Listen, you do me a favor.
You go in there for me

865
01:16:55,844 --> 01:16:56,776
Me?

866
01:16:57,679 --> 01:16:58,771
Why me?

867
01:16:59,581 --> 01:17:03,176
Because you are safe.
There's no way he can hurt you

868
01:17:03,986 --> 01:17:05,749
Go, c'mon

869
01:17:13,528 --> 01:17:14,460
Fine

870
01:17:25,440 --> 01:17:26,737
I am sorry

871
01:17:27,509 --> 01:17:29,101
You know we tried to phone a couple days

872
01:17:29,344 --> 01:17:30,777
but couldn't seem to reach you

873
01:17:32,014 --> 01:17:33,276
He was-

874
01:17:33,649 --> 01:17:35,344
You should've come earlier

875
01:17:44,660 --> 01:17:46,252
He put you up to this!?

876
01:17:47,529 --> 01:17:48,894
How much he pay you huh!?

877
01:17:49,097 --> 01:17:50,086
Jesus

878
01:17:50,632 --> 01:17:52,327
You're so good at reading people?

879
01:17:52,601 --> 01:17:54,159
Can't you see it in my face!?

880
01:17:56,204 --> 01:17:58,331
Leslie, he's gone!

881
01:18:03,145 --> 01:18:04,544
You're lying

882
01:19:13,849 --> 01:19:14,975
Beth

883
01:19:16,518 --> 01:19:17,780
I can't give you the car

884
01:19:20,756 --> 01:19:21,745
Why?

885
01:19:22,991 --> 01:19:24,356
Because the car

886
01:19:27,028 --> 01:19:28,791
the car belonged to my father

887
01:19:32,534 --> 01:19:36,231
Look, he won big one day in a
Hold'em game at the Riviera, and

888
01:19:38,073 --> 01:19:40,507
went out and bought the next day

889
01:19:40,742 --> 01:19:42,334
It was his pride and joy

890
01:19:45,113 --> 01:19:48,981
Til one day I stole his keys,
and an hour later I stole his car

891
01:19:50,118 --> 01:19:51,710
I don't know why I did it

892
01:19:52,053 --> 01:19:53,111
Maybe I just

893
01:19:53,789 --> 01:19:55,814
wanted to see what
he would do, you know?

894
01:19:56,091 --> 01:19:57,285
Was he gonna report it?

895
01:19:57,759 --> 01:19:59,727
Get his daughter arrested?

896
01:20:03,965 --> 01:20:05,899
He did something better than that

897
01:20:06,501 --> 01:20:09,095
He waited until he found
out where I wound up

898
01:20:09,404 --> 01:20:10,462
One morning

899
01:20:10,705 --> 01:20:13,139
a FedEx guy comes
with an envelope for me

900
01:20:13,375 --> 01:20:16,310
Inside the envelope's the title
and registration of the car

901
01:20:20,649 --> 01:20:23,117
Son of a bitch signed it over to me

902
01:20:26,087 --> 01:20:27,145
So

903
01:20:27,889 --> 01:20:30,756
I'm gonna drive this
car until it falls apart

904
01:20:31,026 --> 01:20:32,357
At least until I do

905
01:20:38,233 --> 01:20:40,201
So what am I supposed to?

906
01:20:41,436 --> 01:20:43,927
Well, Beth

907
01:20:45,106 --> 01:20:48,269
I told you I lost everything
back at Harlan's, didn't I?

908
01:20:48,510 --> 01:20:49,534
Yeah

909
01:20:49,778 --> 01:20:52,872
Well, that's not
exactly how it went down

910
01:20:54,115 --> 01:20:57,175
See, I beat that game on its ass, Beth

911
01:20:58,220 --> 01:21:00,552
I knocked them off their feet

912
01:21:01,590 --> 01:21:04,320
The cards turned just like I knew they would

913
01:21:04,593 --> 01:21:06,788
I read the other players just right

914
01:21:09,831 --> 01:21:11,856
I walked away with all their money

915
01:21:12,367 --> 01:21:13,629
So you lied to me

916
01:21:16,037 --> 01:21:17,834
Maybe I didn't want to share

917
01:21:18,406 --> 01:21:21,773
Maybe I just wanted to see how trusting
and gullible you were

918
01:21:23,979 --> 01:21:26,971
Maybe I just wanted company. You know?

919
01:21:27,282 --> 01:21:28,943
It's a long ride, Beth

920
01:21:30,819 --> 01:21:32,582
I didn't want to go alone

921
01:22:11,793 --> 01:22:13,920
Can't do it.
Thirty-five hundred's the best I can give ya

922
01:22:14,129 --> 01:22:16,324
Three thousand. That's my top

923
01:22:16,598 --> 01:22:18,930
Can't. Gotta have thirty-five hundred.
Sorry

924
01:22:19,167 --> 01:22:20,725
Thirty-two hundred.
Take it or leave it

925
01:22:21,002 --> 01:22:21,627
You know what?

926
01:22:21,870 --> 01:22:24,430
I'm sure we can find a better deal
someplace else. Let's go

927
01:22:24,773 --> 01:22:26,832
I don't think you will, ladies.
Suit yourselves

928
01:22:27,042 --> 01:22:28,009
Thank you!

929
01:22:29,945 --> 01:22:30,912
Don't look back

930
01:22:31,279 --> 01:22:32,143
Beth, where are you going?

931
01:22:32,414 --> 01:22:33,210
I want that car

932
01:22:33,415 --> 01:22:34,347
Beth not at that price!

933
01:22:34,749 --> 01:22:37,274
We can get it for three grand
by the time we get to my car

934
01:22:38,119 --> 01:22:39,814
I don't think he's gonna come down

935
01:22:40,088 --> 01:22:42,147
And I think that's the car I want

936
01:22:43,258 --> 01:22:46,227
Have you learned nothing
from your time with me?

937
01:22:46,795 --> 01:22:49,263
You have to stop taking
people at their word!

938
01:22:50,198 --> 01:22:51,597
Maybe you should start

939
01:22:54,369 --> 01:22:55,768
You're hopeless

940
01:22:56,972 --> 01:22:58,132
You're hopeless too

941
01:23:14,956 --> 01:23:16,253
Dear Jeremy

942
01:23:16,825 --> 01:23:20,488
In the last few days,
I've been learning how to not trust people

943
01:23:20,996 --> 01:23:22,588
and I'm glad I failed

944
01:23:32,640 --> 01:23:35,666
Sometimes we depend on other people
as a mirror

945
01:23:35,944 --> 01:23:38,640
To define us and tell us who we are

946
01:23:40,415 --> 01:23:43,646
And each reflection makes me
like myself a little more

947
01:23:45,053 --> 01:23:46,520
Elizabeth

948
01:24:12,147 --> 01:24:13,512
Hello, Cafe Klyuch

949
01:24:53,555 --> 01:24:56,080
Rent

950
01:25:41,536 --> 01:25:42,764
You still open?

951
01:25:43,538 --> 01:25:45,870
No reason for me to
still be here if I wasn't

952
01:25:47,942 --> 01:25:50,604
I heard this place has the best coffee
and pie in town

953
01:25:50,879 --> 01:25:51,777
Where'd you hear that?

954
01:25:52,914 --> 01:25:54,245
I get around

955
01:25:57,752 --> 01:25:58,946
You wanna come inside?

956
01:26:00,655 --> 01:26:01,587
It's cold

957
01:26:02,090 --> 01:26:03,853
What are you doing out here?
It's freezing

958
01:26:04,092 --> 01:26:06,390
It's a beautiful night.
I wanted to get some fresh air

959
01:26:07,896 --> 01:26:09,022
Have a seat

960
01:26:13,902 --> 01:26:15,335
Isn't this reserved?

961
01:26:16,104 --> 01:26:17,230
Reserved for you

962
01:26:23,444 --> 01:26:24,741
Want something to eat?

963
01:26:27,115 --> 01:26:29,208
Yeah, I'm starving

964
01:26:30,451 --> 01:26:31,713
What's good tonight?

965
01:26:32,820 --> 01:26:34,583
What about a steak?

966
01:26:35,623 --> 01:26:36,817
That sounds good

967
01:26:38,092 --> 01:26:39,320
Does it come with home fries?

968
01:26:39,527 --> 01:26:40,551
Or mashed

969
01:26:40,862 --> 01:26:42,022
They both sound good

970
01:26:42,564 --> 01:26:43,895
Half an order of both?

971
01:26:45,567 --> 01:26:47,967
I'll get the home fries with the steak,
medium rare

972
01:26:48,236 --> 01:26:50,329
and a side of mashed potatoes

973
01:26:50,672 --> 01:26:51,866
Coming right up

974
01:27:04,452 --> 01:27:06,113
Learning something about me?

975
01:27:08,022 --> 01:27:09,853
There's something different about you

976
01:27:10,291 --> 01:27:11,883
Or maybe it's me that's changed

977
01:27:14,729 --> 01:27:16,162
Where are the keys?

978
01:27:16,364 --> 01:27:17,695
You don't keep them anymore?

979
01:27:19,567 --> 01:27:21,694
Been trying to give
them back to their owners

980
01:27:22,070 --> 01:27:23,094
Do you want yours?

981
01:27:23,338 --> 01:27:25,966
No. I don't need them anymore

982
01:27:28,810 --> 01:27:30,107
What about your keys?

983
01:27:32,647 --> 01:27:33,875
I got rid of them

984
01:27:37,252 --> 01:27:38,241
Good night, Jeremy

985
01:27:38,486 --> 01:27:39,646
I'll see you tomorrow

986
01:27:54,535 --> 01:27:56,662
You know I came here the night I left

987
01:27:57,372 --> 01:27:59,499
but I didn't make it past the front door

988
01:28:03,344 --> 01:28:06,438
I almost walked in but
I knew that if I did

989
01:28:06,714 --> 01:28:09,478
I would just be the same old Elizabeth

990
01:28:10,885 --> 01:28:12,910
I didn't want to be that person anymore

991
01:28:27,735 --> 01:28:28,929
Hope you enjoy it

992
01:28:39,047 --> 01:28:41,379
Are they still left untouched at the end
of the night?

993
01:28:41,649 --> 01:28:43,412
Yep, more or less

994
01:28:45,453 --> 01:28:47,478
Then why do you keep making them?

995
01:28:51,225 --> 01:28:53,523
Well I always like having one around
just in case

996
01:28:53,995 --> 01:28:56,589
you pop in and fancy a slice

997
01:29:02,003 --> 01:29:04,301
Do you remember that last night
you were here?

998
01:29:06,240 --> 01:29:08,708
When you practically ate an entire pie
all by yourself?

999
01:29:09,944 --> 01:29:11,002
Really?

1000
01:29:12,947 --> 01:29:15,677
I remember getting really drunk and

1001
01:29:15,983 --> 01:29:18,713
having a god awful
hangover the next day

1002
01:29:19,654 --> 01:29:20,848
Nothing else?

1003
01:29:23,524 --> 01:29:25,958
No, nothing else

1004
01:29:31,265 --> 01:29:33,495
Or don't you have a tape I can watch?

1005
01:29:35,303 --> 01:29:37,237
I do... but...

1006
01:29:37,972 --> 01:29:39,530
I've watched it so many times

1007
01:29:39,774 --> 01:29:41,537
that the picture started fading
to black and white

1008
01:29:41,876 --> 01:29:44,208
And now it's completely unwatchable

1009
01:29:44,379 --> 01:29:45,505
Must have been an interesting night

1010
01:29:45,580 --> 01:29:46,547
It was

1011
01:29:52,954 --> 01:29:55,320
Never seen a girl eat
so much in all my life

1012
01:29:58,493 --> 01:29:59,619
Like this?

1013
01:30:03,064 --> 01:30:04,588
No, it was more like this

1014
01:30:12,874 --> 01:30:14,273
It's good pie

1015
01:31:41,996 --> 01:31:44,726
It took me nearly a year to get here

1016
01:31:47,101 --> 01:31:50,070
It wasn't so hard to
cross that street afterall

1017
01:31:51,572 --> 01:31:54,837
It all depends on who's waiting for you
on the other side

